 *
 * !--- locale=En-US ---
 * The NaN, that is, not-a-number, value of the float type. Note that NaN is not equal to any value. In other words, comparisons such as value == NAN cannot be used to determine whether a variable value is NaN. To test for NaN, use the <a href="#nan">nan</a> function.
 */
public const float NAN = ___NAN;

