 *   <dd>The written contents are concatenated as they are.</dd>
 *  <dt>In "wtsv" or <a href="#WRITE_TSV">WRITE_TSV</a> mode</dt>
 *   <dd>The written contents are concatenated with tab separators.</dd>
 *  <dt>In "wcsv" or <a href="#WRITE_CSV">WRITE_CSV</a> mode</dt>
 *   <dd>The written contents are concatenated with comma separators.</dd>
 * </dl>
 * The line break code is automatically chosen appropriately for the execution environment.
 * If you want to use a specific line break code such as <a href="#LF">LF</a> or <a href="#CR">CR</a>,
 * use the <a href="#write">write</a> function instead of this function,
 * and write the content with <a href="#LF">LF</a> or <a href="#CR">CR</a> appended to it.
